The chlorophyll fluorescence parameters of wheat leaves were determined by modulated fluorescence OS1-FL (Opti-Sciences, Tyngsboro, MA, USA) after the completion of each spectrum. First, the dark adaptation clamp was used to adapt the blade to 10 min, and then the initial light energy conversion efficiency of photosystem II (PS II) Fv/Fm was measured, and the calculation was repeated 9 times each time. The formula is as follows:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
